nd (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*syyxH_IeheHtRTwi5IdtdA.png 1400w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lh nj c\" height=\"275\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"700\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"nk nl nm mw mx nn no bg b bh ab ee\">Image generated by author</figcaption></figure><figure class=\"mz na nb nc nd ne mw mx paragraph-image\"><div class=\"nf ng eo nh bi ni\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><div class=\"mw mx pc\"><picture><source sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 1400w\" type=\"image/webp\"/><source data-testid=\"og\" sizes=\"(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*HFLsamyflGT3-TUJuKH0KQ.png 1400w\"/><img alt=\"\" class=\"bi lh nj c\" height=\"275\" loading=\"lazy\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"700\"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class=\"nk nl nm mw mx nn no bg b bh ab ee\">Image generated by author</figcaption></figure><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"7d56\">Sure enough, the results were as expected. With each of the three words, there were a handful of outliers, with some instances of the algorithm finding the target word in 1\u20132, or 7\u20138 guesses (I intentionally let the algorithm run past the official maximum number of attempts of six, otherwise this average would be falsely lowered). Each distribution is clustered around <em class=\"mv\">x = 3</em> to <em class=\"mv\">x = 5</em>, with the majority of the respective solutions being found in that range.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"a9f5\">Just as <em class=\"mv\">later</em>\u2019s rating &gt; <em class=\"mv\">login</em>\u2019s rating &gt; <em class=\"mv\">fuzzy</em>\u2019s rating, <em class=\"mv\">later</em> had a mean number of guesses until the target of 3.81, <em class=\"mv\">login</em> had a mean of 3.88, and <em class=\"mv\">fuzzy</em> had a mean of 4.34. It works!</p><h2 class=\"nq nr gq bg ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on bl\" id=\"6c91\">Wordle Wizard \ud83e\uddd9</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma oo mc md me op mg mh mi oq mk ml mm or mo mp mq os ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"2f8c\">See it in action: <a class=\"ah np\" href=\"https://wordlewizard.streamlit.app/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://wordlewizard.streamlit.app/</a></p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"ccbb\">Excited to show my friends and family what I had made, I\u2019ve deployed the algorithm via a simple web app on HuggingFace, where a user can pass a starting word and target word and my algorithm will solve the puzzle, and show its \u2018thought process\u2019 along the way. This includes the three checks of feedback after each new guess, and it will even show the ratings of many of the remaining possible words if they can visually fit on screen. If you can\u2019t think of any words, it can even suggest some to try.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"ba7e\">After all this, I find myself excited about Wordle again, but now I\u2019m doing Wordle every day, and seeing if I can beat the algorithm. In the future, I\u2019m interested in turning this into a machine learning project; training a model on as many human solutions as possible, and seeing whether, given a certain starting word and target combination, a human would solve it sooner than the algorithm. More to come on this when I get the time.</p><h2 class=\"nq nr gq bg ns nt nu nv nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol om on bl\" id=\"98c5\">Contact</h2><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma oo mc md me op mg mh mi oq mk ml mm or mo mp mq os ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"5e47\">Thanks for reading! If you have any feedback or suggestions, shoot me an email at <a class=\"ah np\" href=\"mailto:kmaurinjones@gmail.com\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">kmaurinjones@gmail.com</a>.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"b0ec\">If you\u2019d like to connect on LinkedIn, you can find me at <a class=\"ah np\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/kmaurinjones/\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.linkedin.com/in/kmaurinjones/</a>.</p><p class=\"pw-post-body-paragraph lx ly gq lz b ma mb mc md me mf mg mh mi mj mk ml mm mn mo mp mq mr ms mt mu gj bl\" id=\"65d5\">If you\u2019re interested in exploring the architecture of this project, you can see its repository at <a class=\"ah np\" href=\"https://github.com/kmaurinjones/Wordle-Wizard-Assistant/tree/master\" rel=\"noopener ugc nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">https://github.com/kmaurinjones/Wordle-Wizard-Assistant/</a>.</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article>";
